Package skeletonlisp.LExp

Class Summary
CondCase CondCase is used for Cond-expressions, it holds one predicate - result-pair.
Lambda Lambda is the data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp's lambda-expressions.
LApplication LApplication is the data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp applications.
LAtom The data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp's atoms.
LCond The data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp's Cond-expressions.
LError LError contains the data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp's error expressions.
LExp LExp is the abstract data-structural representation of a generic SkeletonLisp expression, from which all the different actual SkeletonLisp expressions are derived.
LId The data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp's IDs
LNumber LNumber is the data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp integers.
LPair The class LPair is the data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp's pairs.
LString The LString class is the data-structural representation of SkeletonLisp's strings.
LValue The LValue class is the abstract data-structure that defines all SkeletonLisp's value expressions.
NIL The NIL class is the dataStructural representation of SkeletonLisp's NIL
 

Enum Summary
LExpTypes An enum containing all the types of every legal SkeletonLisp expression
